        <num>CC 3193</num>
        <heading>3193.  Reduction of funeral charges of insolvent decedent</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3193.  Reduction of funeral charges of insolvent decedent.
If the property of the deceased is so incumbered as not to suffice for the payment of his creditors, the funeral charges may, upon the request of any of them, be reduced by the judge to a reasonable rate, regard being had to the station in life which the deceased held and which his family holds.</p>
        </content>
